<br>
As well as resolution, the contrast ratio is important. (Not sure if that's the proper name for it, but it'll be written something like 400:1). This determines how bright and sharp the picture looks (too low, i.e. 200:1) and you get that nasty dark picture that cheap laptops give. You want at least 350:1, preferably higher. <br>
